ce:section.ce:para:
Different dyes-doped silica nanoparticles have been reported such as ruthenium complex Ru(bpy)3
                     2+, fluorescein, tetramethylrhodamine-5-isothiocyanate (TRITC). Silica matrix effectively protects dyes from the surrounding environment, increases photostability, provides signal enhancement for per nanoparticle and does not change luminescence wavelengths [37–41]. Inspired by this, luminol-doped silica nanoparticles (luminol-SiNPs) are designed in the present work and synthesized via water/oil (W/O) microemulsion method in the present work. Spherical luminol-SiNPs with luminol inside the silica matrix can give ultrasensitive electrochemical properties and much higher ECL efficiency than luminol [42]. Luminol-SiNPs are also easy modification and nontoxicity / low toxicity, which is important for ECL nanoparticle emitters in analysis. Since ECL emission of luminol-SiNPs overlaps with the absorption of TNP, ECRET from luminol-SiNPs to TNP is triggered and “turn-off” detection of TNP is achieved (Scheme 1
                     ). Owing to the specific interaction between TNP and LDC, TNP is consumed, and accordingly ECRET from luminol-SiNPs to TNP prevented, which brings “turn-on” detection of LDC. Therefore, a novel ECL donor-acceptor pair of luminol-SiNPs and TNP is utilized and a sensitive ECRET method for both “turn-off” detection of TNP and turn-on” detection of LDC is developed using luminol-doped silica nanoparticles for the first time. More importantly, ECL of luminol-SiNPs is measured via linear sweep voltammetry by electrochemical reduction of dissolved oxygen at negative potential (– 1 V) and in no need of adding hydrogen peroxide (H2O2). Reactive oxygen species be generated in situ and make luminol-SiNPs system emit ECL, which makes ECL of the whole luminol-SiNPs system more stable than luminol-H2O2 system.

As shown in TEM (Fig. 1
                        A–B) and SEM (Fig. 1C) images, the as-prepared luminol-SiNPs display a spherical structure with porous silica matrix, which is in accordance with the reports [40,41,43]. Both the silica matrix and electrostatic interaction retard dyes penetration. After calculated luminol-SiNPs size in TEM images, it can be seen that the average diameter is nearly 33 nm (Fig. 1D). Elements mapping results in supplementary information (Figure S1) confirm the presence of four main elements (C, O, Si and N). Though the dispersion of resuspended luminol-SiNPs is not very ideal, ECL is stable which is of great importance for ECL application. Luminol-SiNPs can be stable for more than 1 month when stored in 4 °C refrigerator by detecting ECL intensity. More importantly, luminol-SiNPs ECL system is no need of adding hydrogen peroxide (H2O2). Dissolved oxygen is electrochemical reduced at negative potential (− 1 V) and then enhances ECL of luminol-NPs at 0.6 V, which makes luminol-SiNPs ECL system more stable than traditional luminol-H2O2 ECL system by monitoring 60 min at room temperature (Fig. 2
                        ). It can be seen that luminol-NPs has stable ECL property.

To evaluate the reliability and potential application of the proposed ECRET system for LDC detection, recovery experiments are performed by standard addition methods in human serum samples. The recoveries of human serum samples spiked with 1 μM, 5 μM and 10 μM LDC respectively are obtained (Table 3
                        ). The average recoveries of LDC in human serum samples range from 93.2% to 101.2%, 96.6% to 101.4%, 95.9% to 102.1% respectively. All the relative standard deviations (RSDs) are lower than 5%. Besides, the proposed ECRET system is also investigated for LDC detection in commercial LDC mucilage standard solution samples. By comparison with LDC mucilage standard solution from three different factories, the average detected content of LDC is comparable with the standard content of LDC (73.86 mM) with relative errors are less than 3% (Table 4
                        ). It is believed that the proposed ECRET system for “turn-on” detection of LDC is accurate and reliable. It shows the high promising for the application of the novel LDC ECRET detection in drug analysis.
